metadata.name: Looking into Medusa's Eyes
metadata.description: Medusa those is a creature believed to turn who look into their eyes to stone in Greek Mythology. snake-haired and sharp-toothed. According to her other Gorgon sisters, Medusa is mortal. Perseus killed Medusa. Medusa, whose beauty is circulating in the languages, living in the temple of Athena, the goddess of intelligence. Athena punished Medusa and her siblings by turning them into demons because of Poseidon, the sea god, Athena's husband, who fell in love with Medusa. According to the rumor, Chrisaor and Pegasus were born from two drops of blood gushing from Medusa's neck when she was killed. The father of the children born is Poseidon.
